        <div>
         <strong>
         </strong>
        </div>
        <div>
         Farm fresh, Choose and Cut Christmas Trees, straight from the grower. Two farms in Auckland: Mangere Bridge and Drury. Open daily, 9am – 7pm.
        </div>
        <h2 style="text-align: left;">
         <a href="http://christmastrees.co.nz/home/retail-price-list/" style="color: #000000;">
          <strong>
           <span style="color: #008000;">
            Auckland Retail Price List 2022
           </span>
          </strong>
         </a>
        </h2>
        <h2>
         <a href="https://www.facebook.com/mountgabriel">
          <img alt="" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-167" height="50" src="http://christmastrees.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/facebook-logo1.gif" title="facebook logo" width="164"/>
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         <!--


<div><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mountgabriel/app/451684954848385"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-579" title="chainsawtreecontest4" src="http://christmastrees.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/chainsawtreecontest41-1024x298.png" alt="" width="640" height="186" srcset="https://christmastrees.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/chainsawtreecontest41-1024x298.png 1024w, https://christmastrees.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/chainsawtreecontest41-300x87.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></div>




<div>Upload a photo of your decorated tree, and get your friends to vote! A winner will be chosen out of the top 4 ranked trees, We’ll pick based on number of votes but also on the trees originality and creativity. Competition closes at midnight Tuesday 22nd of December and we’ll announce the winner after that! The prize is a Makita EA3200S Chainsaw! (Thanks to Onehunga Powertool Centre and Makita Tools for this fantastic prize valued at $508).</div>




<div></div>




<div><a href="https://www.facebook.com/mountgabriel/app/451684954848385/">Click here to Enter</a></div>


-->
        </p>
        <div>
        </div>
        <h2 style="text-align: center;">
         Free Christmas Tree Recycling
        </h2>
        <div style="text-align: left;">
         At the end of the festive season, take your tree to
         <a href="http://christmastrees.co.nz/locations" style="color: #000000;">
          one of our farms
         </a>
         and we will mulch it to use on our fields. Our gates are open just after Christmas and in January so come on down and throw yours on the pile, even if it wasn’t bought from us. Its our commitment to having a sustainable and environmentally friendly Christmas tree farm.
        </div>
        <h2 style="text-align: left;">
         Two Farms in Auckland
        </h2>
        <div style="text-align: left;">
         <a href="http://christmastrees.co.nz/locations" title="Locations">
          <img alt="" class="aligncenter" height="245" src="http://christmastrees.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/locations2.jpg" title="Locations" width="910"/>
         </a>
        </div>
        <h2 style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="color: #000000;">
          The Enviroment
         </span>
        </h2>
        <div style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="color: #000000;">
          We gather our own seed and plant it into our nursery. Then, after years of carefully watching and tending we will take your tree back and mulch into our field to start the cycle all over again. We already have your trees for the next four years planted and waiting for you. So leave your imitation Xmas trees in the cupboard this year so the moths can celebrate Christmas and come on out and get a farm fresh real Christmas tree this year.
         </span>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="color: #000000;">
         </span>
        </div>
        <h2 style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="color: #000000;">
          <span style="color: #000000;">
           Mission Statement
          </span>
         </span>
        </h2>
        <div style="text-align: left;">
         <span style="color: #000000;">
          <span style="color: #000000;">
           To steal the Christmas Tree and give it back to the children of this earth and the grown-ups who still have a child locked deep inside themselves.
          </span>
         </span>
        </div>
